     {q:"Why do scientists analyze the debris produced by high-energy particle collisions?", options:["Particle collisions never produce any detectable byproducts","This concept has no connection to studying fundamental particles","The resulting particles and their behaviour can reveal information about fundamental physical processes","The debris from these collisions provides no useful scientific information"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why are particle accelerators considered valuable tools for testing theoretical models in physics?", options:["Particle accelerators have no connection to testing theoretical physics models","This concept has no relevance to advancing scientific understanding","They allow scientists to create experimental conditions that can confirm or challenge predictions made by theoretical physics","Theoretical physics predictions can never be tested through experimentation"], answer:2}
