     {q:"Why is the Theatre of the Absurd considered a significant movement in the broader history of drama?", options:["This movement had no lasting influence on the history or development of drama","The Theatre of the Absurd never actually challenged any existing theatrical conventions","It fundamentally challenged traditional ideas about narrative structure, meaning, and purpose in theatre","This genre has no connection to broader developments in dramatic art"], answer:2}
