     {q:"Why is the concept of convergence, applied consistently across both integrals and series, considered a unifying theme in advanced calculus study?", options:["It shows that seemingly different infinite processes can be analyzed using closely related reasoning about limits and boundedness","This concept has no relevance to deepening a student’s understanding of calculus","Integrals and series are entirely unrelated processes with no shared mathematical structure","Convergence has no meaningful application to either improper integrals or infinite series"], answer:0}
